  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 40.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And again he came, and found them sleeping, for their eyes were very heavy",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "καταβαρυνόμενοι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ")",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": ":",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " literally, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "wei",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "g",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "hed down.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " They had not deliberately yielded themselves to sleep; but an oppressive languor, the effect of great sorrow, had come over them, so that they could not watch as they desired to do; but by an involuntary action they ever and anon slumbered. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "They wist not what to answer him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". They had no excuse, save that which he himself had found for them. Mark 14:40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
